data.name: rtbForest.Text
data.value: In the Serene Forest, competitors will have plenty of cover. Somewhere in these woods lies an abandoned temple and an old watchtower. The name may sound peaceful, but this arena will witness events that are anything but.

data.name: rtbChangelog.Text
data.value:
Additions: -- Added Status Effects, which can affect the outcome of battles: added Burning, Poison, and Freeze -- Added the Forest Imp Encampment landmark for characters to find alongside the temple and watchtower -- Added rain, which has a 10% chance of happening every day -- Added the option to cure status effects and imbue weapons with effects on the sponsor screen -- Added a Sorcerer's Staff, which can be found only in the watchtower after defeating the Living Dummy -- Added a shrine to the abandoned temple that can boost a player's weapon attack by 2 -- Added the Estus Flask and Chug Jug healing items, which are the new best in their rarity tier -- Added a randomize button to the sponsor screen to pick a random sponsor (or not one at all) -- Added a game option to change starting health -- ???
Changes: -- When an opponent is spared in a battle with more than 2 characters, they flee instead of being left in the battle to possibly attack the one who spared them -- When a character heals during battle it shows the name of the healing item -- A character can now loot the healing item of a slain enemy if they have one -- When a character's weapon attack is boosted the name of the weapon changes to reflect that -- Lowered the threshold from 8 health to 5 health for healing being the chosen value on the sponsor screen, and made hunger a higher priority than weapons -- Buffed the values of already existing healing items to reflect the addition of Status Effects -- Nerfed the damage output of the flamethrower and blowgun, but they cause Burning/Poison now -- Tracker Jacker attack lowered, but it now causes Poison -- The winner's remaining health and their final weapon is shown on the winner's screen
Fixes: -- Fixed it to where a healing item will be saved if any of it would be wasted -- Fixed it to where the correct form of "a" vs "an" will be used when finding weapons -- Fixed Killer Frost temperature -- Fixed spelling of sandwich
